            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2008-10-16 10:27:34 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>In the Classic theme the &quot;selectbox&quot; appearance is based on the &quot;button&quot; appearance. This appearance sets the &quot;center&quot; property, which is only available for all widgets based on Atom.
Since the selectbox widget is based on the generic widget class it does not offer the &quot;center&quot; property.

Modify the &quot;selectbox&quot; appearance to fix this problem.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>5856</commentid>
            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2008-10-16 10:53:49 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Better approach: Insert an indirection &quot;button-frame&quot; as in the Modern theme. This way the &quot;center&quot; property is only set in the &quot;button&quot; appearance and all appearance which only need the frame of the button can use the &quot;button-frame&quot; appearance.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
